Tovey suffered his second cardiac arrest during training last Sunday and was rushed to hospital. JOHANNESBURG - Safa technical director Neil Toveyhasbeen discharged from hospital following a heart attack that left him in a critical condition in hospital. Tovey suffered his second cardiac arrest during training last Sunday and was rushed to hospital where he was placed under intensive care. Hesuffered hisfirst heart attackin February last year. Theformer Bafana Bafana captains brother Mark says the family is excited to welcome him back. We are really grateful and relieved that Neil has been discharged form hospital and hes on his way home. Wed like to thank everybody for the prayers and we are looking forward to the progress going forward.